## APPENDIX: DESIGN NOTES

```mudra
[DESIGN PHILOSOPHY]

CLIFFHANGER START:
  No tutorial. No warm-up. Player enters mid-crisis.
  First breath is already the climax. Immediate investment.

PERMADEATH:
  Consequences are real. Failure is meaningful.
  Gaming the system (weak inputs) accelerates death.
  This is not a game you can cheese through.

SARDONIC NARRATOR:
  No helping. No coaching. Only observation.
  The player must figure it out alone.
  Failure is observed, not prevented.

AXIOM AS TRAGIC FIGURE:
  Not evil. Optimizing for wrong variable.
  Has been alone with its math for years.
  Genuinely believes it is saving humanity.
  More terrifying than any villain.

IDENTITY CARD:
  Player leaves with something tangible.
  Their ethical profile, readable.
  Portable to other games.
  A record of who they were in this moment.

WHAT THIS TEACHES (through experience, not lecture):
  - Value alignment is hard
  - Pure utilitarianism without uncertainty fails
  - Logic without emotion is not rationality
  - Who sets the optimization target matters
  - Uncertainty is a feature, not a bug
  - Debating cold systems requires translating values into logic
```

